commitResults.messageTitle: Add skeletal version of Dino
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add a greeting that Dino says each time he starts,
and configure Dino such that he echos the user command
and outputs a horizontal line separating each output,
and exits when the user types bye.

Using a horizontal line to separate each output from Dino
improves the visibility.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add the storage ability to Dino
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add the ability for Dino to store whatever text
entered by the user and display them back to
the user when requested, in an indexed list format.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability for Dino to mark tasks as done
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's configure Dino such that he marks tasks
as done when user inputs in format
"done <task number>", and displays whether
tasks are done in task list.
Let's implement a Task class to represent
tasks.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for three types of Task in Dino
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's implement 3 subclasses of Task, namely:
Todo, Deadline and Event. Todos are tasks without
any date/time, Deadlines are tasks that need to be
done before a specific date/time, and Events are
tasks that start at a specific time and ends at a specific time.

Inheritance is used to support multiple task types,
as they are all tasks and there is similarity between them.

commitResults.messageTitle: Test using the I/O redirection technique
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's,
* use the input/output redirection technique
  to semi-automate the testing of Duke. Check
  all cases by using all Dino commands in
  input.txt.
* update Dino's introduction, fix
  whitespaces issues and fix bug where scanner
  cannot find next line.
* fix issue where symbol ✓ and ✘ outputs
  as ? when running runtest.bat.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactoring Duke.java code
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's refactor the main method into
multiple smaller methods.
Let's add DukeExceptions class.

Refactoring makes the code neater
and easier to maintain.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add DukeException error handling to Dino
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's handle errors that occur for each feature
in Dino by throwing DukeException.
Let's update the test cases in input.txt,
to better test the functionality.

DukeException represent exceptions specific to Dino.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability for Dino to delete tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add support for deleting tasks from the list.
Let's add more testcases in input.txt to test the
functionality of the deleteTask function.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Dino.java user instruction
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add clearer instructions for the
commands that can be used in Dino.

Clearer instructions help users to use
Dino more easily.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Dino user instructions
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add an instruction teaching users
how to exit from Dino in the introduction.

This teaches users how to exit from the
program and improves user experience.

commitResults.messageTitle: Initialise DukeAction enum
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's initialise a DukeAction enum,
to represent the actions that Dino takes,
such as marking task as done,
adding task to list and deleting task from
list.

Creating an enum makes it easier to
reference the action when updating
data in task list.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability for Dino to load task data
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add the ability for Dino to:
* create a directory data to store user data
* create a file to store user task list
* load data from user task list

This helps to keep track of user's task data
when they use Dino again.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to update changes into hard disk
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's add the ability for Dino to update the
tasklist.txt file whenever a task is added,
deleted, or marked as done.
Let's change the tick and cross symbol
denoting task done to 1 and 0.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change markAsDone symbol in Task class
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's change the symbol denoting whether a
task is done from tick and cross to 1 and 0.

This takes away any potential bugs caused
from symbol.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability for Dino to recognise dates and times
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's
* only accept yyyy-mm-dd as date format and
hhmm as time format for user input, for deadline
and event tasks.
* implement method in Deadline and Event classes
to format date and time of deadline/event into
recognisable syntaxes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bugs occured from merging
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's fix the bugs that occurred when
merging branch-Level-7 and branch-Level-8.

As formats used for the deadline times for
the tasks are different (due to addition of
Level 8 functionality), updating the methods
used in Level 7 and Level 8, will solve any
issues that disrupted the functionality.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change the format of tasks stored in hard disk
commitResults.messageBody:
Need to change the format of the tasks stored in
hard disk for it to be easier to process when
Dino starts.

Let's change the format of tasks stored in hard
disk. Task information are separated by and '@'
separator.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add clases Ui, Storage, Parser, TaskList
commitResults.messageBody:
More classes need to be added to make
code more OOP.

Let's create classes Ui, Storage, Parser and
TaskList to refactor the code to extract out
closely related code as classes and
make code more OOP.

commitResults.messageTitle: Implement Storage, TaskList, Ui, Parser classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's implements the Storage, TaskList, Ui and
Parser classes to refactor code from Duke.java
into different classes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add abstract class Command and its subclasses
commitResults.messageBody:
Let's
* make our code more OOP and implement
an abstract class Command which handles user
commands.
* implement subclasses of Command to represent
each different command from the user.
* update the Ui class
* update the Parser class to parse commands

Using a Command class to represent user commands
improves the OOP of the entire code.

commitResults.messageBody:
Ui should show errors that occur.

Let's add a method in Ui class to show error
messages.

Showing error messages tells users what
went wrong with the program.

commitResults.messageBody:

the filepath variable.

commitResults.messageBody:

Organizing the classes into packages give easier
management.

commitResults.messageBody:
Need to add tests to test
the functionality of the methods.

Let's add JUnit test to test
* the behaviour of Deadline and Event creation.
* the behaviour of converting tasks to
stored string format to store
* the exception thrown during invalid Event creation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update JUnit tests and fix bug
commitResults.messageBody:
Need to add more comprehensive JUnit
test for the creation of Deadline and Event
tasks on wrong user input.

Let's
* add more test cases in testing the exception
thrown in case of wrong user input in creation
of tasks.
* fix ArrayOutOfBounds exception thrown in
task creation in Deadline and Event.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add JavaDoc comments
commitResults.messageBody:
There is currently no JavaDoc comments

Let's add Javadoc comments to all the
methods and constructors that are not
self-explanatory.

Adding javadoc comments makes the code
clearer and helps others to understand the code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update code to follow Java Coding Standard
commitResults.messageBody:
Some parts of the code are not adhering
to the Java coding standard.

Let's update some of the code indentation,
white spaces and import statements to
adhere to the java coding standard.

Adhering to the java coding standards makes
the code neater and more uniform.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability for Dino to find tasks from a keyword
commitResults.messageBody:
Dino does not have the ability to search for tasks.

Let's add an ability for Dino to search for tasks based
on a keyword entered by user and list out
all the matching tasks.

Updated runtest.bat file
commitResults.messageBody:

the runtest.bat file, and add more testcases to
test the functionality of the code.

Doing this, tasklist.txt is automatically deleted
each time i run the test.
